inn1.comm: good length ball, just around off, he is across to defend
hint of swing into the left-hander, just a hint as he pitches this close to off, Jamshed arrests his across movement and defends
there is the bit of inswing again, but heading down leg as Jamshed misses the nudge and is hit on the pad
is careful now after the inward shape and softly tucks this pitched up ball to square leg
bowls it with some angle now, taking it outside off  stump, Jamshed stretches forward to block
right forward to block to extra cover as Panyangara ends a steady over with a length ball on off
hint of straightening into the right-hander with a pitched up ball on off stump, driven back to the bowler
lovely, hits a good length as it comes in to Shehzad, but then carries away with the angle and bounces after pitching, past the outside edge
worked in the air behind square, Williams stops it with a slide
goes across, opens up and defends as Vitori gets another one to bounce,
nice inswing, but it has started outside leg stump and will carry further down
corrects the line a tad but it is still ending on leg stump and is worked down to fine leg
comes across and just outside off, getting behind the line of a length ball to play it out to leg
presses forward to a pitched up delivery on off and pushes to covers
nice, hurled up just outside off and holds the line, excellent, confident leave too
early step forward to smother a pitched up delivery
angles it in, draws him forward into a prod, and moves it away sharply past the edge
now this one jags in and kicks from wide of the crease, the previous one went away, Shehzad is moving across thinking about the away shape probably, and is hit on the body
pitched up now and defended off the front foot
angles it in but too far into the pad, and Jamshed tickles it past short fine
into leg stump again but holding the line and Jamshed checks the push to mid on
pitched further up, middle and leg, but Jamshed is not committing into the clip through his favoured on side, checks the shot again to mid on
played softly again, this was full and straightening outside off, and Jamshed knocks it wide of extra cover
goes for the drive through midwicket now as this is pitched fuller on off, but ends up inside edging to square leg
nudged to the leg side for a quick single
holds the line from a good length into the left-hander who nudges it down to fine leg
forward to solidly defend to extra cover
good delivery, inviting the drive with a fuller length and shaping away, left alone
this is tight stuff from Zimbabwe, another one pitched up close to off, Pakistan have been quite cautious, no risk taken so far
turns a length ball but midwicket is onto it and non-striker has to get back
first attempt at a drive and Shehzad pings the small gap at cover-point off the front foot, it is pulled back inside with a slide
just short of driving length, he stays back and pushes down the pitch
width now, back of a length, and Shehzad gives it direction with a meaty punch past a diving point
Vitori comes back strongly, bowls it full and quick on the stumps, Shehzad gets a leading edge to third man as he eyes the on side
holding the line, good length, outside off, softly guided to point
full, drew him forward, but started far outside off and moved away a lot, and he pulled bat away
Jamshed goes for the gap at midwicket and picks it with a firm clip, mid on chases
pitched up outside off, Jamshed forward but checks the drive and picks up one to extra cover
bounces from just short of a length, and he awkwardly knocks it out into the off side
fuller and with lots more zip, he defends swiftly off the front foot
pitched up, Jamshed is not going after it, these openers want to bat long today, defended to mid off

and then next delivery he offers a simple chance, edging off the back foot to the slip cordon, where it is promptly spilled,  it is Sibanda at second slip who drops it, moving to Hamilton Masakadza's left at first slip, nice height, above the knees, debatable as to whose take it was, but it was highly takeable
stabbed down to third man
worked wide of mid on for a comfortable single
floated up a touch too full, and Jamshed places the drive past mid off's dive
guides a length ball holding the line outside off, to point
bouncer, dug in quite short, Jamshed looks at the square leg umpire, the wide call does not come, it should have, that was clearly looping above Jamshed's head
this one will be called wide alright as Vitori sprays it down leg with the angle
was a chance, quite difficult one, Jamshed tickled a bouncing delivery off the pad, Taylor dived a long way to his right, but it eluded him
and Vitori sends another one down the leg side, looking for another strangle chance probably
then he decided it is time for some correction, and does a whole lot of it, swinging it away wide outside off
it is over finally, Vitori gets one off a good length on off stump, and Jamshed defends it to leg
holds the line from a fullish length outside off, he comes forward, opens the face and runs it to backward point
on middle, but he goes across and nudges it in front of midwicket for a quick run
slanted across the left-hander, too far across
fine comeback, moves it away off the seam from back of a length, past the outside edge
and again, more effort on this one angled across, Jamshed beaten again on the forward push
Jamshed is finding it hard at the moment, a thick edge runs to point now as he shapes up to defend
stays in the crease and defends a length ball safely
whippy length delivery bouncing outside off immediately, left alone
hurled in full now at the stumps, driven to extra cover with an open face
zings it across the left-hander, but too far to make him play
better line, going across closer to off stump, Jamshed walks across and leaves
punched past point, third man runs around
bounces from a good length awkwardly, he handles it well, playing it down behind point
full, widish and driven, straight to extra cover
checks the push to a full one but times it nicely down the pitch, and straight into the stumps at the other end, it ricochets wide of mid on
into middle and off, he gets bat around front leg in time and works it to midwicket
Panyangara has been superb with this delivery, just back of a length, across the left-hander, just enough seam movement to beat the edge, on another day ...
good length, defended off the front foot
and is in business right away as Jamshed picks up an easy single with a nudge

dropped, once more, it is Williams this time at extra cover, Shehzad got one full for the drive and went after it, straight to Williams and straight out, Panyangara manages a smile, wonder what he's feeling inside
hits the pad and pops up in the air close to the pitch
length ball left alone outside off
good length, defended to covers
pitched up on off now, he is right forward to block
short of a length, bouncing close to off, left alone
wants the single after pushing a length delivery, but extra cover is quick to run forward
worked off the pad to square leg
tossed up slow, outside off, defended
fuller, pushed in front of extra cover
flatter, he goes across and works it to midwicket
goes further across and knocks it square for one
good length, turned to midwicket

and when they manage to take one, the ball does not carry, inches short of Hamilton Masakadza as he falls to his right, it is the short of driving length, Shehzad pushing at one that moves a tad away after pitching
left alone outside off
moves back foot towards the leg side now as the bowler runs in, but allows it to pass by outside off
far too wide and helped away past point, the sweeper keeps them to two
pitched up and angled in to middle, clipped down to mid on
back of a length, steered to third man
tossed up on leg, he cannot work it away
stinging connection on the sweep, and Shehzad beats deep square leg's sprint and dive to his right
floated full outside off, pushed down to long off
spins away now from off stump, he stays in the crease and guides it behind point

nicely done, Utseya gets the breakthrough after the dropped catches, floats it up across from round the stumps, Shehzad drawn into a hard push, drags the back foot out as he misses, it is pinned just outside the line as Taylor breaks the stumps, square-leg umpire gives it right away
on the front foot to defend
pitched up middle and off, Jamshed hasnt been able to time the clip through midwicket, mishits to mid on
neat, softly pushed in front of covers for a dash to the other end
thick outside edge flies towards point but falls well short as Hafeez is opened up by a skiddy short of a length ball
uncertain at the start as always Hafeez, a late decision to leave and the ball pings the bat to roll to the slips, there are two of them
good length, played out carefully to covers
this zips into the right-hander, who jabs it square, where the fielder makes a sliding stop
tossed up slowly, close to off, defended
slightly flatter, good length, hurries on as he plays off the back foot
goes for the cut now to a similar delivery close to off but finds point
fuller, around the pad, he cannot beat midwicket
moves forward and drags a drive wide of long off for two
good length, some spin into the pad, nudged square
full and going across, but very close to off stump, Jamshed hasn't been in the mood to drive big and pushes to mid off
middle and leg line, Jamshed tucks it fine, but the fielder runs across to his left in the deep and cuts off the boundary
cramped for room on this short of a length ball as he gets too across, chops it behind point
nice, that has taken off from short of a length, and a surprised Hafeez is beaten
Hafeez smiles, this is a fine early examination for him, good length this time but skidding past the edge, Hafeez does not attempt to prod away from the body this time
gets bat on this one and plays it out to mid on
fuller length on and around off stump. Driven to long off by Jamshed
fuller length pitching just outside off. Hafeez tries to squirt this past point but finds the fielder
fuller length again and Hafeez gets forward to drive this through the off side
length ball on leg and middle. Punched in the gap at mid on as the batsmen look to complete two, but Panyangara sweeps on it quickly and prevents the second. Good effort
fuller length on middle and off and Hafeez dances down the track to hammer this over long on for a six

dropped fuller length ball just outside off. Hafeez once again dances down, this time aiming for deep extra-cover. Times this sweetly enough to carry to the man on the boundary, but ends up botching the attempt and padding the ball over the boundary rope for an assisted six. Very positive from Hafeez
pitches on a length on middle and angling away. Played to the off side for none
length ball angling away on a middle stump line. Jamshed hangs his bat as the ball rushes past the edge on its way to the keeper
short of a length on middle and leg. Jamshed works this behind square leg for a single
length ball pitching outside off and slanting in. Punched to mid on for a single

fuller length just outside off. Jamshed gets forward to drive through cover, but with minimal footwork, as he ends up getting a thin edge, which carries to the keeper. The Zimbabweans go up instantly and the umpire confirms the decision with a raise of the finger. Big wicket for Zimbabwe
length ball outside off and angling in. Defended to the leg side by Misbah
flighted and just outside off, Hafeez makes room and guides it towards short third man
length ball on middle and off. Misbah steers this in front of square on the leg side for a single
fuller length outside off and Hafeez advances down before driving past the bowler through long off
fuller length, same line, and Misbah gets into position quickly to reverse-sweep this past backward point for a boundary
length ball on and around off. Misbah tries to work this away behind square but finds the fielder
fuller length outside off. Misbah finds the fielder on the leg side
length ball pitching outside off. Hafeez plays to the off side
fuller length on middle and leg. Hafeez attempts a clip off the pads but to no avail
short of a length outside off. Hafeez defends to the off side
short of a length outside off and Hafeez defends back to the bowler
length ball and Hafeez steps down immediately, but then decides to abort a stroke as he allows it to carry to the keeper
length ball outside off and Hafeez shoulders arms. Maiden over from Chatara. Good, tight bowling this morning from the Zimbabwe seamer
fuller length outside off. Misbah tries to work this away to the leg side
fuller length again and Misbah defends to the leg side
short of a length and Misbah gets back to defend to the bowler
fuller ball pitched wide of off stump. Misbah tries to steer this square on the off side, but doesn't make any contact with the ball
tossed up and on off, Misbah prods forward and blocks
fuller length just outside off and Misbah is able to work this away square on the leg side for a single
short of a length and well outside off, Misbah steers it towards third man
short of a length swinging down the leg side and immediately called a wide
short of a length pitched wide of off stump. Hafeez rocks back to play this off the back foot through cover
short ball pitching outside off and slanting in. Hafeez read it early as he gets back to pull this behind square for a boundary which beats fine leg
full and outside off, Hafeez gets forward and drives it towards cover
length ball angling in and Hafeez works this away to the leg side
length ball which is played to third man
fuller length on middle and Misbah tries to work this behind square on the leg side
fuller length outside off and Misbah plays this under his eyes and takes off for a quick single. Hafeez gunning down for the striker's end and is able to beat Chigumbura's throw to the keeper.
length ball just outside off. Defended back to the bowler
length ball again on the same line. Hafeez shuffles down and whacks this over long on for yet another six. Hafeez has certainly taken a liking to Utseya today
length ball pitching outside off. Hafeez gets back and tries to steer this through cover, but finds the fielder
length ball that is punched to the leg side for none
fuller length just outside off. Misbah drives this authoritatively, but finds mid off
fuller length angling down the pads. Misbah tries to clip this but doesn't get sufficient bat on it
length ball pitching just outside off. Misbah drives this through mid off, but finds the fielder
short of a length outside off and Misbah defends to the leg side
short ball well wide of off stump. Misbah sticks his bat out to hit this in front of square on the off side for one
fuller length pitched outside off. Hafeez drives this straight to mid off
fuller length on middle and Misbah steers this to the leg side for one
short of a length outside off and Hafeez tries to work this away on the leg side
length ball on the same line. This time Hafeez is able to steer this square on the leg side
short of a length and Misbah plays a short-arm pull for one
short of a length and Hafeez nudges this in the gap on the leg side between short fine leg and midwicket
Waller drops one short and just outside off, pulled down to long on for a single
short of a length and Misbah gets into position quickly, helping it on its way through third man for three
fuller length on and around off. Defended to the off side
short of a length and Hafeez gets back to clip through square leg
short of a length on the off stump. Misbah gets back and works this away to long on
fuller length outside off. Hafeez gets forward and nudges it in the gap through cover
length ball on middle and leg. Misbah fails to work this away behind square leg
full toss outside off and Hafeez gets on the front foot and drives this sweetly through extra-cover for a much-needed boundary
length ball on middle and leg. Hafeez glances this behind square
fuller length on middle and leg. Misbah steers this to the leg side
short of a length on middle and off. Hafeez gets deep in the crease to cut this away in front of square for another boundary. Hafeez showing good intent so far this innings
length ball outside off and once again Hafeez gets into position effectively, and squirts this behind point for another four
length ball on middle and leg. Hafeez nudges this through the leg side for a quick single. Some confusion from the batsmen, as Misbah wanted a second, but denied by Hafeez
short of a length on middle and leg. Defended back to the bowler
fuller length outside off. Misbah steps back to drive this through cover
fuller length on middle and defended back to the bowler
fuller length outside off and Hafeez gets forward to drive this through extra-cover to bring up a well-earned fifty. He is providing the impetus this innings, while Misbah plays the anchoring role
flighted and on middle, Misbah presses forward and blocks
length ball on middle and leg. Hafeez nudges this to the leg side for a quick single

good length delivery on the leg stump, Hafeez softly flicks it past short fine leg, the ball races away to the fence but the fielder gives chase, puts in the dive and just pulls it before the boundary
good length delivery on the stumps, Hafeez defends
short and just outside off stump, Hafeez goes back and just cuts it very late past backward point and it easily runs away to the third man fence
good length delivery outside off stump, Hafeez guides it to third man
full and on the pads, Misbah flicks it along the ground to deep backward square leg

full delivery, almost yorker length, and Hafeez tries to drive this through cover, coming forward slightly, but misses it and then drags his foot back to the crease as the keeper fails to pick up the ball and stump Hafeez. Near miss from the Zimbabweans
tossed up on the off stump, Misbah comes on the frontfoot and blocks well
full length picked up on the full and Misbah drives this through long on for three
flighted delivery on the leg stump, Hafeez flicks it to backward square leg
length ball on middle and Misbah defends back to the bowler
nicely bowled from Williams, slower through the air on the off stump, Misbah softly defends
floated up outside off stump, Misbah drives it to mid off
full delivery outside off and this one is squeezed behind square to third man
short of a length outside off and Misbah gets back to cut this behind square to beat the boundary rider at cover for a boundary. Only the second of his innings in his 33 off 39
length ball on middle and leg. Defended to the leg side
length ball on off and Misbah angles this to the leg side for a quick single
short of a length outside off and Hafeez shoulders arm
length ball outside off. Hafeez defends to the off side
length ball on middle and leg. Misbah steps back and cuts this in front of square
fuller length and Hafeez defends to the off side
length ball outside off and Hafeez dances down to drive this through extra-cover
length ball on middle and Misbah uses the same tactic of stepping back and getting deep in the crease before working it away square on the off side
fuller length on off and middle. Hafeez drives this to long off
full length outside off and Misbah drives this to extra-cover
pitching on leg and Misbah works this away to deep square leg
length ball on middle and off. Defended back to the bowler
length ball on the pads and Hafeez works this away square on the leg side
fuller length outside off and Misbah unable to get it away behind square
fuller length on the pads and Misbah pushes this to the leg side
short of a length and Hafeez quickly into position to cut this away through deep extra-cover
length ball that carries straight to the keeper. Misbah failed to make any connection on it
length ball outside off and once again Misbah unable to get any bat on it as he went fishing for it
short of a length on the same line. Misbah gets some bat on it but it ends up ricocheting behind
length ball on the same line. This time Misbah gets forward to drive uppishly towards mid off
fuller length just outside off and Hafeez defends to the off side
short of a length and well wide of off stump. Immediately called wide by the umpire
on a length and Hafeez attempts to cut this behind square, but finds the fielder
tossed up, turned from outside off in front of square leg
makes room but Utseya follows him with a full one into the leg side, Hafeez cannot get under it and swats it past the bowler along the ground
Misbah heaves but cannot get much of a connection, the ball rolls behind square leg
backs away to leg again and takes this off middle to dab it past the keeper
flat, good length ball, worked through square leg, they rush back for the second
spinning down the leg side, Hafeez tries to help it away, finds short fine leg
tries to whip it over midwicket but thick-inside-edges through square leg
hit down to long on
moving outside leg, Chatara follows him, Misbah has to squeeze it out to the off side for a quick single
gone now, slower one does it, it was bowled very wide, Hafeez tried to run it between backward point and short third man but only spooned it up to the latter
not that far outside off, flashed down to square third man
Misbah shuffling about, dragging back foot to the leg side, then walking across outside off, and working a full delivery in front of square leg
kicks a bit from a good length and Misbah has to knock it back
turned straight to square leg
Misbah connects, turning the face to hit this pitched up ball over midwicket and wide of long on

Amin is gone on the second run, after facing just one ball, it was always going to a tight attempt as they decided to go for the additional run after a whip behind square leg, the throw was at the right end, the bowler's, and was spot-on, Amin had a long way to cover, he didn't help himself at all by hesitating in responding to Misbah's push for the second
knocked close to the pitch on the leg side for a single
he gave this swipe everything he has, and he has a lot, but didn't connect
full on the pad, nudged away, but midwicket is around to prevent the single
would have been a wide down leg, but Afridi has sent it racing past short fine leg, reaching out and turning it with swift hands
beaten on the inside edge, was looking to dab it to third man but it has come in from short of a length
another almighty swipe, another miss to a length delivery
spot on, just back of a length on middle, even Afridi has to show it respect as he blocks
length ball into the pad, turned for short fine to make a sliding stop, and that is yet another fifty for the Pakistan captain, he's like the safest of banks
knocked back to the bowler
he's making room outside leg, but bowler's followed him, this is in the blockhole too, and dug out
uh oh, asking for trouble, half-tracker to Boom Boom, and he smashes it behind square leg
pitched up, hit straight to midwicket
goes outside leg stump, takes it on the full and drives past extra cover, long off does really well to deny them the second
good length, starting outside leg, he plays it out
not much room on this one either but he manages to squeeze a drive to extra cover and calls early
that kicked, from short of a length, but it was down leg, he wanted to nudge it fine, but it hit the glove and popped towards short fine leg
he's had one swipe too many at these length deliveries, and edged this one into the keeper's gloves
good length, around off, pushed from the crease to covers
tries to squeeze it to the off side but gets too far across and ends up pushing down the pitch
walks across and pushes a full delivery to extra cover, wants the single but this has gone straight to the fielder
punched to mid off, not getting the single again
loose, comes out and has a push at a length delivery, Panyangara has been taking them away from the left-hander all morning, and Sohail is beaten
overpitched and smashed through the covers, but the sweeper is in place
Misbah creates another single, walks outside off late, to a length ball, and nudges it to square leg
almost in the blockhole outside off, guided straight to backward point
charges out and cuts as Vitori drags the length back, but third man will prevent the second

hello, how is this even possible, calling this a blinder is a huge understatement, Sohail has bashed this widish length delivery, Utseya is there at shortish extra cover for the uppish drive, but this is a full-blown cross-batted thunderblow, Utseya has leapt to his right, taken it one-handed, and come down on earth with the ball lodged safely in his hands, once he realises it has stuck, he allows himself a relieved celebration, holding arms aloft
defended off the back foot
length ball pushed to point
ducks under a bouncer
that looks close, Vitori shouts for the lbw, but umpire shakes his head, hit him right in front, probably pitched outside leg, nope, replays show that pitched leg stump, that was plumb
walking across to turn it to leg, and hit on the pad but outside the line of off
length ball punched past the non-striker
a low full toss follows the batsman as he backs away to leg, driven down to long on
full on off, driven down to long on
low full toss on the pad, whipped out to deep midwicket
short of a length, Misbah does not have any width, so he makes sure he drops it softly to the off side for an easy run
bouncer, avoided safely as he sways inside the line
cuts this late and cuts well, but straight to backward point, they take one as it bursts out of his hands
Misbah walks to off and nudges a pitched up ball to midwicket
excellent line, good length on middle, starting outside leg, can't get under it, and knocks it back
overpitched down the pads, and flicked to deep square leg
into the pads from wide of the crease, can't connect with the bat, as ball rolls away square

chance at deep midwicket as Misbah picks this from well outside off, Sibanda had to run in, he did, he went for the catch as opposed to saving the boundary, he dived forward too, but it swept past and over the rope
Chatara shouts for lbw, but batsman was a long way down the pitch as he missed the flick, possibly just outside the line of off too
good length, slower one, pushed to covers for one more
another length ball, knocked to backward point
back of a length bouncing on middle, he chops it but backward point is around to prevent the run
squeezes a length delivery past cover to the sweeper
Misbah reveals his ploy by backing to leg very early, Vitori follows him with a length ball and only a guided single to point results
he's played a couple of deft late cuts now, but each time has picked out backward point

he's been given by the third umprire, Sarfraz had set off for what seemed to be a dangerous second in front of square leg, but looked to have made it with a massive dive before Taylor took the bails off, taking the ball in front of the stumps, that didn't make for easy decision making on the replays, but at worst there was doubt on this one, and at best, Sarfraz's bat was safely in, stunned glances all around from Pakistan, from Sarfraz, Misbah, and Whatmore
an appeal for leg before as he misses a fullish one, had to have pitched outside leg, else Ajmal was gone
full toss into the pad, driven down the ground, Maruma runs across from long on and dives to save the boundary
charges out and swings hard but cannot beat the sweeper
pitched up and angled in, goes looping past midwicket
tries the ramp over short fine leg, but ends up scooping it towards third man, falls short
Misbah backing to leg again, Chatara digs it in short, Misbah crouches, it goes past his helmet, he's not getting the wide call
walks across and turns it off middle to fine leg
Misbah takes off late, is waiting deep in the crease and tees off, lofting a length ball onto the roof beyond long-on
back in the crease again, but this one is much fuller, and he can't get enough under it, he refuses the single as the ball squirts square
turns down another single as he whips to deep square leg
right in the blockhole now, and Misbah can only dig it out
connects big second time in the over, it is a full toss this time and mowed over deep square leg

Zimbabwe end the innings with another dropped chance, extremely hard one though, Misbah slices this full delivery over point, fielder runs back, dives but cannot take it, Misbah is happy with two, and Sarfraz has to get back

inn2.comm: short of length ball, well outside off and left alone
length ball on leg stump, coming into the batsman and bounces up to make Masakadza look awkward
short of length outside off, left alone. The keeper is taking these well above his chest
slightly closer to the stumps on length, left for the keeper again
full on the pads this time and Masakadza is beaten by pace, big appeal for lbw but it pitched outside leg
length ball on leg, tucked on the leg side where a short midwicket is in place
pitches it on leg and it swings down further for a wide
another wide down the leg side after swinging down
much better as Junaid pitches it on length outside off and it angles away from the batsman
down the leg side, there was some noise as it went past the batsman and it's been given a wide
length ball on the stumps, defended back with a straight bat
length ball on off, driven straight to extra cover
short of length on off, Sibanda goes back and defends it to point
length ball on the pads again, Sibanda fails to connect with the bat and manages a quick leg bye
length ball outside off, Masakadza shoulders arms without trouble
short ball well outside off, it bounces off towards the keeper
full on the pads, Sibanda misses again as he tries to drive on the on side and there's another lbw appeal but it pitched outside leg again
length ball outside off, defended off the back foot to point
length ball outside off, driven firmly form the middle straight to mid-off
short of length outside off, punched off the back foot between extra cover and point and they run three and Sibanda has opened his account
length ball outside off, guided to third man with an open face of the bat
short of length on the middle stump, it zips into the batsman who is beaten by pace and bounce
length ball outside off, Masakadza stays back and cuts it in style between third man and point for his first four
length ball outside off, Masakadza drives on the front foot but missed as it angled away
length ball closer to the stumps, defended to point
slightly short on off, Masakadza stays back and defends to point
length ball outside off, driven handsomely but the fielder at cover dives full length to his right to save some runs
full outside off, driven and timed to perfection by Sibanda to pierce it through the covers for four
full on off, driven down straight just wide of mid-off for a single
flighted on middle and leg, pushed down to long-on
flighted again, tucked to midwicket this time
short of length on off, pushed back to the bowler
flighted on off, defended back to Hafeez
slightly slower, the batsman comes forward and defends
slightly short on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
flighted on middle, turned to midwicket
short on off, pushed wide of mid-off for a single
on leg stump, turned to short fine leg
tossed up, flicked off the pads for four by Masakadza
tossed up on the stumps, turned to deep square leg
short and outside off, punched back to the bowler
flighted on off, pushed back to the bowler
straight ball driven to long-on for a single
slightly short, pushed to long-on
short ball turned to midwicket
full on leg, turned to short fine leg
flighted on off, defended
short of length, punched to long-on
quicker on the pads, missed by the batsman
flighted on off, guided to point
flighted on off, inside edge goes to the leg side
flighted on off, pushed to point
short of length, punched down the ground to long-on
full delivery drive to long-on
short of length, turned to midwicket
flighted ball on leg, turned to midwicket
quicker one on the stumps is defended
flighted ball defended on the front foot
flighted outside off, pushed to cover
short of length on off, punched to long-on
flighted one on middle, turned to midwicket
flighted on off, pushed to cover for a single
quicker one on off, pushed to cover again
short of length on off, driven to deep cover
short of length outside off, driven to sweeper cover
flighted on off, pushed to cover
short of length on off, pushed to cover
fuller length, played to midwicket
shorter ball on middle and leg, played to midwicket
fuller length and played towards midwicket
tossed up on middle and leg, driven to long on
fuller length, Hamilton shuffles down and drives wide of the bowler for a single
short ball on leg, Sibanda goes back in the crease and works this behind square to fine leg
short ball outside the off stump. Hamilton gets back and cuts this to deep cover
fuller length on middle and leg, Sibanda gets forward and drives to long on
lofted shot over extra cover, Irfan pulls it back at the boundary
tossed up outside off, squeezed to point off the front foot
fuller delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and defends
slow and loopy outside off, driven to long off for a single
slightly short on the middle stump, the batsman goes back and punches it to long on
on the pads, the batsman turns it to backward square leg for an easy single
quicker delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and defends it solidly
back of length delivery, the batsman defends it close to the stumps and steals a single
length delivery outside off, the batsman allows it to come to him and then steers it down to third man
fuller delivery outside off, the batsman wanted to drive it through covers, but gets a thick edge down to third-man
back of length delivery on off, defended to cover off the back foot
similar delivery, same result as the batsman pushes it to cover
slightly fuller and wider, the batsman wanted to push it through covers, but gets no timing, straight to Misbah at cover
flighted and on the pads, the batsman turns it to the leg side and takes off for a quick single. The keeper runs for it and fires a throw to the non-striker's end, but it was all safe
stays on the back foot and chops it on to point
comes forward and pushes the fuller delivery to deep cover
short and slow on off, the batsman goes on the back foot and punches it to deep cover
tossed up on the stumps, the batsman dabs it to the left of the cover fielder for a single
he gets a leading edge, but it just lobs over the bowler's head! He was looking to turn that to the leg side
he finds the boundary to get close to team's 100! This was only slightly short, but there wasn't much pace on it and the batsman pulls it to the cow corner easily
short of length on off, the batsman whips it towards deep square leg to bring the 100 of the partnership
he beats the bat with one that keeps going away with the angle! the batsman plays inside the line
back of length on off stump, the batsman dabs it to the fielder at cover
only slightly short! and look at Vusi, he smashes it to the deep midwicket boundary to bring up his fifty!
he whips the length delivery past midwicket for a single
tossed up outside off, it's the straighter one. the batsman plays it late towards short third man
slow and slightly short outside off, the batsman waits on the back foot and pushes it to deep backward point

there is the wicket! He does it all the time, Saeed Ajmal! After two straightish deliveries, Ajmal sends down the conventional delivery and Vusi had no clue about that. He stayed back in the crease, saw the ball turning in after pitching, but played outside the line to be hit straight in front of off and middle. Easy decision for the umpire
quicker delivery this time to the new man, muted appeal from the bowler, but there was some bat on that
interesting now! Taylor decides to sweep one from outside off and gets a thick top edge that just falls short of Irfan at fine leg
tossed up delivery, driven to long on for a single
full and outside off, thick outside edge goes to third man
full on off, pushed to leg side for a single
length ball on the stumps, defended on the back foot
short and wide outside off, cut to deep cover and that's his fifty
short of length outside off, pushed to point
fuller length on off and middle. Hits the pads and a stifled appeal goes up, but the umpire is not interested
short of a length on middle and leg and Hamilton gets into position to play a paddle sweep through fine leg which beats backward square leg to the boundary
length ball on middle and leg. Pushed to mid on for none
length ball pitching outside off. Hamilton tries to get bat on it but narrowly misses the edge on its way to the keeper
length ball on middle and leg. Hamilton hits this straight to midwicket
length ball pitching on off and angling away. Taylor drives straight to extra-cover
length ball on middle and leg. Defended back to the bowler
length ball on and around off stump. Taylor opens the face and steers to third man
length ball on middle and off. Hamilton drives to extra-cover
short of a length wide of offstump. Taylor plays an uppish drive through extra-cover for a boundary. Good forceful shot from the Zimbabwe captain
length ball outside off and Taylor steers this straight to backward point
short of a length on leg stump, Hamilton plays this to midwicket
short of a length on off stump, Hamilton gets back and pushes this past the bowler
short again outside off stump, Hamilton cuts this behind square to third man
fuller delivery from Ajmal, which Hamilton pushes to cover
fuller length on off stump, Hamilton steps down and lofts over mid on for a boundary
fuller length on off and is defended back to the bowler by Hamilton
fuller length on off stump, Taylor plays this to cover
length ball on off stump and is pushed by Taylor to the off side
length ball again just outside off, Taylor guides this to third man for a single
short of a length wide of off stump, Hamilton cuts this to deep cover for a single
length ball which is defended back to the bowler
length ball pitching outside off. Hamilton flashes hard through the off side, but finds the fielder
fuller delivery on middle and leg, angling down the pads. Hits the front pad but the ball was always going down the leg side
length ball outside off and Hamilton cuts this fiercely behind square
length ball outside off. Defended to cover
fuller length just outside off and Taylor gets forward to sweep this behind square for a well-timed boundary
length ball and defended back to the bowler
short of a length pitching on off and middle. Hamilton drives this off the back foot to long off
length ball on middle and leg. Defended back to the bowler
length ball on middle and Taylor defends to the leg side
length ball on middle and defended back to the bowler

fuller length on off stump and Taylor plays an improvised paddle sweep, with the intention of beating backward square and the boundary rider square of the wicket. Goes up and falls in no-mans land. Lucky escape for the captain
short ball which Hamilton is content to let through to the keeper
fuller length on middle and leg, hits the thigh of Taylor
length ball outside off. Taylor drives this to cover
fuller length outside off and Hamilton clears his front leg to play a lofted shot over extra-cover which carries all the way to the boundary for six. What a wonderful shot from Masakadza!

full length on middle and leg. Hamilton plays this straight back to the bowler, but Afridi, being casual with the return, lets it through as the batsmen are able to scamper two quick runs to put the Pakistani fielders under the cosh
flighted delivery outside off, Masakadza defends it to the off side
overpitched and in the slot. Masakadza picks it and absolutely murders it between extra cover and long off
fuller length on middle and off. Driven to long on by Taylor
length ball pitching outside off and turning in. Hamilton works it away to the leg side
pushed through quicker, Masakadza punches it towards mid on
short outside off, Masakadza pushes it back to the bowler
flat and outside off, Masakadza punches it down to long on
short of a length outside off. Taylor angles this square on the leg side
fuller length on middle and leg. Taylor works this away through midwicket
full length on middle and leg. Hamilton drives this to the right of the bowler down the ground
length ball outside off and Taylor plays a lovely lofted shot over extra-cover which beats long off to the rope
angling into the pads, Taylor clips it away to backward square leg
full delivery on and around off. Defended back to the bowler
length ball pitching outside off and angling in. Defended to the off side
turning into the pads, Taylor works it away to mid wicket
fuller length outside off. Hamilton backs away to make room on the off side in order to free up his arms, but is unable to make a connection
flighted delivery outside off, Masakadza defends it to covers
flighted delivery on off, Masakadza eases it down to long on
fired in full on off, Taylor eases it down to long on
fuller length outside off. Hamilton hits it down the ground to long on
fuller delivery which is defended back to the bowler
length ball on middle and Hamilton gets back to play a drive to mid off for a single
short of a length on middle and off. Defended to the off side
length ball on middle and leg. Taylor quickly gets into position to play a more squarish reverse-sweep, but finds the fielder on the off side
fuller delivery pitching on off and middle, hits the front pad and the Pakistanis go up in appeal. Umpire turns it down. Ajmal can hold the key here
fuller length pitching outside leg. Taylor sticks his bat out and is able to steer it in front of square on the leg side for a quick single
fuller length on off and middle and Taylor gets forward to play a sweep shot behind square which beats the boundary rider at deep square leg
fuller length pitching just outside off and Taylor steers this to midwicket for one
length ball pitching on and around off. Defended to the leg side
length ball outside off. Played straight back to the bowler
fuller length outside off and Hamilton pounces on it, playing yet another lofted shot over long off for a boundary
turning in sharply on a middle and leg stump line. Hamilton tries to whisk this away on the leg side, but to no avail
length ball on and around off stump. Defended back to Ajmal
length ball on the same line. Taylor tries to work it away but finds the fielder on the leg side
short of a length on leg stump and Taylor glances this to backward square leg

short of a length pitching just outside off. Hamilton, who makes a last minute adjustment to get on the back foot, hits this directly to Misbah, who is stationed at short cover. Still eight wickets in hand, but Zimbabwe would have badly wanted Hamilton to push on for at least a hundred. Pakistan with an opportunity here to tilt the scales
length ball on middle and defended back to the bowler
fuller length on middle and leg. Maruma able to get bat on it as he squeezes this square on the leg side for a quick single
what a jaffa from Irfan! length ball on middle and completely sqaures up Maruma as it passes the blade on the way to the keeper. What a start from Irfan in this second spell
fuller length on the same line and this time Maruma is able to steer it square on the off side for a single
fuller length on middle and leg. Squeezed away square on the leg side
fuller ball pitching just outside off. Maruma gets forward to play an expansive drive but is beaten by the pace
fuller length again, just outside off, and Maruma content to let it through to the keeper
fuller length pitching wide outside off and left alone by Maruma
fuller length just outside off and this one is the doosra as it spins away from the batsman on the way to the keeper
another doosra, this time pitched wider. Maruma not picking the doosra at all
tossed up and turning in this time, Maruma gets forward and defends it solidly
short of a length and pitching on middle and leg, before turning into the pads sharply. Huge appeal from Pakistan but is denied as it was pitching outside off
flighted delivery outside off, Maruma gets down and sweeps it to deep square leg
length ball outside off, Maruma tries to cut it behind square on off but misses
length ball outside off, Marume leans forward and runs it down to third man for a single. There is a short third man too, to stop that single

short ball outside off, defended to point off the back foot and the fielder has a direct hit from there so they're going upstairs. But Maruma has made it in time and he's been given not out. They also took an overthrow after the direct hit
length ball on off, defended back to the bowler
short of length on middle and leg, defended on the back foot and Maruma was a long way down the pitch and rightly sent back by Taylor
length ball on off, defended to point and Maruma is halfway down the pitch again. The fielder throws the ball to the non-striker's end and he is back in time again. The pressure is building up here
short and flat just outside off, Maruma fails to cut the ball
slightly slower on middle, pushed back to the bowler
the wrong one on off and the inside edge goes to short fine leg. They scamper for a single and Taylor dives to make his ground, desperate to take the strike
quick and full on the pads, turned to fine leg for a single
quick and full on the pads, Maruma has lofted it down the ground and it falls just short og Ahmed Shehzad at long-on and oh, he's missed it for a four!
short and quick just outside off, Maruma cuts it fine past the keeper and they take two to keep Taylor on strike
short of length outside off, pushed to point
length ball on off, jabbed to point and they take a quick single
full on off, Maruma brings his bat down and a thick edge goes to third man
length ball on the stumps, Taylor makes a bit of room and drives it between extra cover and point for a single
length ball on the stumps, Maruma heaves at it and it's gone high up in the air, will somebody catch it? No, the top edge it's gone for six over third man!
he goes after it again and this time the leading edge falls into the hands of Ahmed Shehzad at point after taking the aerial route. An innings full of edges and tension comes to an end
length ball on the leg stump, turned square of the wicket on the leg side and the batsman take two
length ball outside off, turns away and punched to cover where Misbah stops it, but not cleanly, and saves some runs
Williams comes down the track and drives a length ball to long-off for a single
dropped! Taylor reverse swept a low full toss and backward point drops it on his left hand side
on the pads, turned to square leg for a single
Williams comes down again and drives down the ground for a single
full on the pads, turned to deep square leg, a lot of cries from the pitch for a quick throw and a fumble gives the batsman time for two
length ball outside off, driven with ease to sweeper cover
length ball on the stumps, Taylor makes room but can't get it past point
short of length on the pads, turned to deep square leg for a single
length ball outside off, Williams cuts and an inside edge goes fine down the leg side for four. That one hit the leg stump just after the edge but the bails didn't budge!
full and angled towards leg stumps, driven down to long-on for a single
flighted on off, Williams leans forward and sweeps it on the leg side for a single
short and flat on middle, turned to short fine leg for a quick single
length ball on the pads, Williams came down and just managed to get some bat to run it fine past Irfan at short fine leg for four. It's tilting towards Zimbabwe now
another four. Ajmal tossed it up a bit and Williams sweeps it from the middle of the bat to the square leg boundary for four
slower outside off, Williams waits for it and pushes it on the off side
quick and full on off, driven down to long-off with ease for a single
almost a yorker on the pads and Williams can't connect it while trying to turn it on leg
right in the block hole, Williams just plucks it out but not past the bowler
half-volley this time and Williams cashes in by driving it to the left of long-on for a couple. Not a clean pick up by Nasir Jamshed in the deep
cracking shot! Short ball on the stumps and looks like Williams knew it was coming there, he smacked it to the midwicket boundary, nobody moved.
low full toss on the pads, driven down to long-on for a single
short on leg, Taylor pulls awkwardly because of the bounce and it goes in the air but falls safely behind midwicket for a single
tossed up on off, pushed towards point for a single
tossed up on off, Williams comes down and drives it back to the bowler
tossed up on middle, driven down to long-on
flighted on the leg stump, turned away easily to square leg for a single
flighted and full outside off Williams reverse sweeps it very fine for three
flighted on leg stump, pushed on the leg side
length ball on off, defended to point and Williams is sent back for the single

it's all over! Irfan pitched it up and Williams has smoked that in his favourite area - the cow corner for a six! Whattay way to finish the match, whattay way to start the series, whattay way to cheer the crowd!
